div.p:
Our current relations with the Soviets are clouded in part because of
                            escalating public rhetoric in both countries. The Soviets are reacting
                            with increasing bitterness to attacks on “détente” in this country;

—however, we now find that more work remains to be done and that the
                            commitments of the senior cabinet officers are such that we cannot
                            schedule the required high-level meetings during the next 10 days;

—Secretary Kissinger has informed
                            me of your proposal to conduct bilateral consultations over the coming
                            year;
